snE3ZuXhcHgAVt3xTUGgzQ
This is the type of bar you hit first on the bar crawl nights. It's fun, the bartenders are super friendly and attentive, and the crowd is a big mish-mash of young, old, ethnicities, skinny, fat, skinny fat and what not. It almost feels like an intimate neighborhood bar at times.  However, it seems each time I've gone in on the weekends, the place clears out around 10-1030 when everyone heads to a dance club.  Still it's fun, especially Thursdays when they have a trivia night. I miss my old team, Anal Beads & Things.  Plus, it's right off the light rail between the stops for Osborne and Thomas, so you can ride there, go home, or ride to one of the bars on the light rail path!

